00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Conversation 1

10
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
We are down to two candidates for one position,

11
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:49,000
and we need to decide by the end of the day in order to finalise this whole procedure.

12
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Yes, but it isn't an easy choice to make. Both applicants are quite strong.

13
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Let's get to it then. Both of them went to good universities,

14
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
and both of them studied business-related subjects.

15
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:06,000
So academically, I'd say they're pretty much the same. What do you think?

16
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
I would agree, yes. The only difference worse noting perhaps,

17
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,000
is that it looks like Rachel scored moderately stronger grades throughout high school and university.

18
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
But as I said, only a tiny bit higher than Peter.

19
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
That's true, and worth noting, thank you.

20
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:25,000
In addition, Rachel interviewed very well.

21
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
I thought she came across as bright and alert.

22
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Yes, she asked some very good questions about the position and the company,

23
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
which made me think she is very keen about the job.

24
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,000
I thought so too. Now let's look at Peter's interview performance.

25
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,000
I thought he also did very well.

26
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:45,000
He came across as respectful and professional, wouldn't you say?

27
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Calm and poised. Very mature for his age.

28
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Exactly. In my notes, I wrote that he seemed composed and in control of his emotions.

29
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
I think he definitely looked more mature than Rachel.

30
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Interesting. So we agree that Rachel appeared inexperienced and less mature than Peter.

31
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Even though both candidates are the same age and have practically no work experience.

32
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:16,000
When comparing them side by side, yes, Peter seems more self-assured somehow.

33
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Maybe it was something about their body language.

34
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Sure, maybe he was simply less nervous.

35
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Maybe. Who knows? To be honest, I think I like Rachel better.

36
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Hmm, really? I think I like Peter.

37
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Well, if there's a tie and we can't come to an agreement, then we'll take it to John

38
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
and let him cast the deciding votes.

