Conversation 2. We're here with Clementine Ortega, head designer of the private fashion label, Laurentge.

45
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:10,000
To discuss her latest collection, Ms. Ortega, how would you describe this season's look?

46
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:18,000
To be honest, my preferred style has always been on the ambiguous side, and I think this collection is even more so.

47
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:22,000
I try not to adhere to social norms and expectations.

48
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Rather, I always try to incorporate something slightly absurd into my aesthetic.

49
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:33,000
The assortments of accessories in this collection have had quite the impact on critics.

50
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:39,000
The dazzling cape deployed at the end of the show, for example, bewildered many in the audience.

51
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:42,000
What was your inspiration for this piece?

52
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:50,000
Over the summer, I traveled through rural mountain villages throughout Asia, in search of handicrafts to decorate my new studio with.

53
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:57,000
The embroidery done by the women in a particular village was so exquisite, I couldn't stop thinking about it.

54
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Trying to recreate their designs would have been futile, so instead I applied my own eccentric approach.

55
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Using glitter, I drew similar intricate patterns onto the velvet cape.

56
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:15,000
This ended up in the glamorous luminous look that concluded the show.

57
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:20,000
It was indeed majestic, and yet there I say masculine at the same time.

58
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:27,000
Well, yes, that was intentional. I like to merge styles that are often at opposite ends of the fashion spectrum.

59
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Hence, the sparkling cape was paired with a traditional power suit you would typically see in a business setting.

60
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
It was sensational if I do say so myself.

61
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Spectacular for sure. A stunning show all around.

62
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:49,000
Going against stereotypes, the incorporation of indigenous aspects, along with your underlying signature touch,

63
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,000
made this collection a statement of the season.

64
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:59,000
You have proven yourself a formidable young designer, and we can't wait to see what creations you come up with next.

