Passage 1. Pet dogs can often readily understand a wide range of their owner's commands and gestures.

77
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:56,000
But are these abilities inborn or are they exclusively learned through training?

78
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:03,000
To find out, a new study examined whether stray dogs could understand human gestures.

79
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:11,000
The study revealed that 80% of participating dogs successfully followed pointing gestures to a specific location.

80
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Despite having never received prior training.

81
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:21,000
The results suggest that dogs can understand complex gestures by simply watching humans.

82
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:27,000
This could have implications in reducing conflict between stray dogs and humans.

83
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:32,000
Dogs were domesticated 10,000 to 15,000 years ago.

84
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:37,000
This means they are probably the oldest domesticated animals on the planet.

85
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:46,000
Humans then bred dogs with the most desirable and useful traits so that they could function as companions and workers.

86
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:53,000
This resulted in domesticated dogs that are highly responsive to human commands and gestures.

87
00:08:53,000 --> 00:09:01,000
However, it was not clear whether dogs understand us through training alone or whether this was an inherent ability.

88
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,000
Why does this matter?

89
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Stray dogs are a common feature in cities around the world.

90
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:11,000
They may observe and occasionally interact with people.

91
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:16,000
But such dogs have never been trained and are behaviourally wild.

92
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Conflicts between stray dogs and humans are a problem.

93
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Understanding how humans shape stray dogs' behaviour may help alleviate this problem.

94
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:33,000
According to the researchers of the new study, stray dogs are intelligent creatures.

95
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:39,000
They closely observe humans and use their understanding of us to make a decision.

96
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Treating stray dogs with sensitivity and respect and giving them space the researchers assert can reduce much conflict.

